-- в”Ђв”Ђ Xata в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Xata is a serverless Postgres database platform offering instant copy-on-write branching, scale-to-zero compute, and both fully managed cloud and bring-your-own-cloud deployment for engineering teams.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$usage-based$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free open-source self-hosted core; Xata Cloud from about $0.012/hour compute plus $0.28/GB/month storage (roughly $9/month for a micro instance)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2020, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Xata Review 2026: Serverless Postgres Pricing and Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Xata offers serverless Postgres with instant branching and scale-to-zero compute. See how its usage-based pricing and open-source core compare for dev teams.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Xata is a database infrastructure company founded in December 2020 by Monica Sarbu, with CTO Tudor Golubenco, headquartered in San Francisco. The company raised a 5 million dollar seed round led by Index Ventures in 2021 and a 30 million dollar Series A led by Redpoint in March 2022, notable at the time for having an all-women board. Xata originally launched as an Airtable-style serverless data platform built on top of Postgres and Elasticsearch, but underwent a significant product rebuild between 2024 and 2025 to reposition itself as a dedicated serverless Postgres platform centered on database branching. The current product lets developers create and branch Postgres databases the way they branch code in git. Using copy-on-write storage at the storage layer, each branch shares underlying data with its parent and only stores the changes made within that branch, rather than duplicating the entire dataset, which makes branch creation close to instantaneous even for large databases. Xata separates compute from storage, enabling scale-to-zero behavior where idle compute costs stop accruing without deleting data, combined with high availability through multi-availability-zone read replicas and automatic failover. Databases support both the native Postgres wire protocol, so existing Postgres clients and drivers work unmodified, and SQL over HTTP for serverless and edge environments. Xata's business model has three tiers. The Apache 2.0-licensed open-source core can be self-hosted for free, though with a roughly 10-second cold-start wake time and community-only support. Xata Cloud is the fully managed, pay-as-you-go offering, billed at about 0.012 dollars per hour for compute (roughly 9 dollars per month for an always-on micro instance) plus 0.28 dollars per gigabyte of storage per month, with instance sizes scaling up to 8xlarge configurations priced around 1,121 dollars per month; Cloud includes SOC 2 and GDPR compliance and multi-region deployment on AWS and GCP. The top BYOC (Bring Your Own Cloud) tier deploys into a customer's own cloud account with HIPAA-ready anonymization, 24/7 support, and multi-cloud region support, priced via custom quote based on the number of concurrent database branches needed. Xata is best suited for engineering teams that want git-like database branching for preview environments, CI testing, and safer schema migrations, while staying on standard Postgres rather than adopting a proprietary database engine.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '0dfbc077-2e6f-43bd-beb1-5237a10ecdd5';

