-- в”Ђв”Ђ Xnapper в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Xnapper is a macOS screenshot beautification app that automatically adds polished backgrounds, padding, and framing to screenshots for sharing on social media, in docs, and in presentations.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free with watermark; $29.99 one-time for 1 device (Basic plan)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2022, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Independent, solo-founder product$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE(NULL, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Xnapper Review 2026: Pricing, Features and Mac Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Xnapper turns plain Mac screenshots into polished, shareable images automatically. See pricing from free to 49.99 dollars one-time, features, and alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Xnapper is a native macOS screenshot application created by indie developer Tony Dinh in 2022, built to solve a specific problem for content creators: turning a plain screen capture into a polished, presentation-ready image without opening a design tool. Dinh built the app after his own frequent need to share screenshots on Twitter and LinkedIn, where visually appealing images perform better than raw captures. The core workflow captures a screenshot in about two seconds, then automatically balances the composition by adding padding, a rounded-corner window frame, and an appropriate background, using smart background selection to pick colors or gradients that suit the captured content. Beyond the automatic styling, Xnapper includes a privacy-focused redaction feature that can automatically detect and blur sensitive information such as email addresses, IP addresses, credit card numbers, API keys, and passwords before an image is shared. It also uses Apple's built-in Vision framework to extract and copy text directly from a captured screenshot, functioning as lightweight OCR without a separate tool. Additional capabilities include custom gradient and image backgrounds, window capture, annotation tools such as arrows, shapes, text, and blur, screenshot history, configurable keyboard shortcuts, and presets sized for common social media platforms. Xnapper follows a freemium, one-time-payment pricing model rather than a subscription: the app is fully usable for free, with a watermark applied to exported images, and a one-time purchase removes that watermark. As of current pricing, three one-time tiers are offered based on the number of Mac devices licensed: Basic at 29.99 dollars for one device, Personal at 39.99 dollars for two devices, and Standard at 49.99 dollars for three devices. The app has built a loyal following among independent creators and startup founders, with the company reporting roughly 4,000 creators using it daily and a 4.9-star average rating. Xnapper is best suited for individual content creators, indie developers, and product marketers on macOS who regularly share screenshots publicly and want a fast, no-subscription way to make them look polished.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '75b7cec6-4a39-4456-8f5f-bb719bb42775';

